title: For Sale:  FS: Vintage Crosman 160 (2nd Variant) - Good Condition
postcontent: Up for sale is a vintage Crosman 160 .22 cal., single shot airgun. It is the 2nd Variant, with the automatic safety. It runs on two CO2 cartridges. It has a rear sight and a peep sight installed. The condition of the metal is about 80% and the wood about 75%. It's in good condition for it's age and appears well lubricated inside and out. The bore is pristine and the barrel has a very nice crown. The wood also has a nice grain pattern. There is some light rust on the peep sight, and possibly other places. The rifle holds air and shoots at about 450fps in 50 degree weather. It should definitely shoot faster in warmer weather, as is standard for CO2 power. It may also need to be resealed to bring up the speed. Two new o-ring seal kits are included. I hoped to reseal it, to gain a few more fps, but I'm going to pass on doing this work in favor of other projects. This is a very nice looking, hard-to-find airgun in great condition. It is sold as-is.
